{"_id":"8zdiyDzn3UJ3dXHR","name":"Pale One Blessings","type":"feat","img":"systems/frontierscum/tokens/players/pale-one.webp","data":{"description":"<p>You are literate, but only in dead languages, and cannot use scrolls. Instead, you can intuitively use one randomly rolled Power. The Power changes each dawn, or dusk (pick one).</p>\n<p>1. THE STARS WERE RIGHT <br />&nbsp; &nbsp; Roll d4+2 for omens. Say something cryptic every time you use one.</p>\n<p>2. MEMBRANOUS WINGS</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; You can fly short distances, but cannot wear armor. Birds seem to dislike you.</p>\n<p>3. UNCOMMON CLAY</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; You can draw nourishment from soil, but normal food makes you sick. You smell like mushrooms.</p>\n<p>4. MANA FROM SOMEWHERE</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Spend a use of your Powers to create food for d6 people. It is weirdly delicious, but unsettling.</p>\n<p>5. DIGITIGRADE LIMBS</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; You can escape any bindings, and fit through tiny spaces. Tests involving flexibility are -4 DR.</p>\n<p>6. TOO MANY EYES</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Just way too many. You cannot be attacked from surprise. You can spend a use of your Powers to leave an eye behind, and spy on a remote area. If anyone squishes the eye, you take d2 damage</p>","rollFormula":"","rollMacro":"","rollLabel":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.frontierscum.class-esoteric-hermit.HVtEy2VmsOh5aBOE"}}}
{"_id":"S1S18jcbMvIbTFR9","name":"Creature Shape","type":"feat","img":"systems/frontierscum/tokens/players/cursed_skinwalker.webp","data":{"description":"<p>Give into the advances of your antithetical other and change your very anatomy into the likeness of its being. Shifting your bones as such occupies a single painful round. Armor and weapons are likely unusable in your new form. One (1) of the following creatures stands ever at the other side of your existence:</p>\n<p>1. MURDER-PLAGUED RAT<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &bull; Tiny: Agility tests, including defence, are DR8.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &bull; Your bite (d4) carries disease, victims test DR14 Presence or attack their closest ally, until either is dead.</p>\n<p>2. FLAYED AND DRIPPING WOLF<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &bull; Ferocious, attacks are DR10.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &bull; Your fangs (d6) crit on a natural 19 as well as a 20. On a crit, all enemies test Morale.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &bull; Slick from blood, -d2 incoming damage.</p>\n<p>3. BONESKULLED RAVEN<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &bull; Fast and flying, defence is DR10. Make two attacks per round with your claws (d4).<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &bull; Your bony scalp (d6) acts as a weapon and a shield: -1 damage and you may choose to ignore all damage from one attack. The skull will heal in d6 days.</p>\n<p>4. BEAR FROM BERGEN CHRYPT<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &bull; Hulking and massive: tests for Strength and Toughness, as well as attacks, are DR10. Defence is DR14.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &bull; Thick hide, -d4 incoming damage.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &bull; Your claws and bite deal d8 damage.</p>\n<p>5. LIFE-AND-DEATH-LIZARD<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &bull; Regenerate d4 HP per round.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &bull; Bite (d6) or spit acid (d4, 1 in 4 chance armor is lowered one tier).<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &bull; Scaly skin, -d2 incoming damage.</p>\n<p>6. DOOMSAYING MONKEY<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &bull; Dextrous: Agility tests, including defence, are DR10.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &bull; Light armor and weapons remain usable.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &bull; Your third eye allows you to read unclean scrolls at DR10.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","rollFormula":"","rollMacro":"","rollLabel":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.frontierscum.class-gutterborn-scum.UTqe9O4NGgUOloZG"}}}
{"_id":"U8xOFkDlKMbUO419","name":"Pale One","type":"class","img":"systems/frontierscum/tokens/players/pale-one.webp","data":{"abilities":"<p>Wise, roll 3D6+2 for Presence. Weak, roll 3D6&minus;2 for Strength. Ordinary starting equipment plus one random scroll (sacred or unclean). Roll a D4 on the weapons table and D2 on the armor table. You also begin with one of the following:</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Master of Fate</li>\n<li>Book of Boiling Blood</li>\n<li>Speaker of Truths</li>\n<li>Initiate of the Invisible College</li>\n<li>Bard of the Undying</li>\n<li>Hawk as Weapon</li>\n</ol>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Eldritch Origins, d6</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Awakening, adult, in a ritual circle underneath the northern bridge to Grift.</li>\n<li>Wandered, memoryless, from the mouth of a cavern at the cliffs of Terion.</li>\n<li>Single child survivor of an incident in the Valley of the Unfortunate Undead.</li>\n<li>Dying of plague in a Bergen Chrypt hovel, you touched something from outside.</li>\n<li>An average individual until you encountered something in a dim glade in Sarkash.</li>\n<li>Raised on a lonely island in Lake Onda. No one else has ever heard of this island and you can&rsquo;t return.</li>\n</ol>","armorTableDie":"1d2","description":"You lurk on the fringes of settlements, observing, perhaps judging, but rarely interacting. You are fundamentally other, and belong nowhere. Youâ€™ve had bouts of incoherent madness and self-destructive rages, but mostly you simply wait, in solitary resignation, for that which is inevitable.","omenDie":"1d4","startingAgility":"3d6+1","startingHitPoints":"1d6","startingItems":"frontierscum.class-pale-one,Pale One Blessings","startingPresence":"3d6+1","startingRolls":"frontierscum.rolls-pale-one,Unspoken  Origins,1\nfrontierscum.rolls-pale-one,You Call Yourself Subtable 1,1\nfrontierscum.rolls-pale-one,You Call Yourself Subtable 2,1\nfrontierscum.rolls-pale-one,You Call Yourself Subtable 3,1","startingSilver":"1d6*10","startingStrength":"3d6","startingToughness":"3d6-2","weaponTableDie":"1d6"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.frontierscum.class-esoteric-hermit.ifSBk6ORiHgq3Xhr"}}}
{"_id":"wBWpa9Ob9ki9FwsO","name":"Cursed Skinwalker","type":"class","img":"systems/frontierscum/tokens/players/cursed_skinwalker.webp","data":{"abilities":"<p>Weakened mind, roll 3d6&minus;2 for Presence. <br />Bestial instincts, roll 3d6+1 for Strength and Toughness. <br />Roll d6 on the weapon table and d2 on the armor table. <br />Abilities</p>\n<p>@Item[S1S18jcbMvIbTFR9]{Creature Shape}</p>","armorTableDie":"1d2","description":"You should have died, but something grabbed a hold of your soul as it seeped into the river of Death and sealed you once again in mortal flesh. Only this time the cage is not yours alone-in the currents of the afterlife your soul mingled with that of another dying creature, leaving you halved. Now you live a shared existence, locked in everlasting struggle between man and monster. You should have died.","omenDie":"1d2","startingAgility":"3d6","startingHitPoints":"1d8","startingItems":"frontierscum.class-cursed-skinwalker,Creature Shape","startingPresence":"3d6-2","startingRolls":"frontierscum.rolls-cursed-skinwalker,First Died,1","startingSilver":"1d6*10","startingStrength":"3d6+1","startingToughness":"3d6+1","weaponTableDie":"1d6"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ExGbll5H7WY8LROo":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.frontierscum.class-gutterborn-scum.gAx8MWLiZcjiWQvc"}}}
